      "content": "- **Basic nitrogens (CYP2D6 key feature):**  \n  The molecule contains **amide/imide-like nitrogens** (a carboxamide `...C(=O)N...` and an N within a **highly carbonyl-substituted bicyclic imide/urea-like system**). These nitrogens are **not meaningfully protonatable at physiological pH** due to strong resonance with adjacent carbonyls \u2192 **low basicity**.\n- **Aromatic/lipophilic features:**  \n  One **phenyl ring** (benzyl substituent) plus a **bicyclic hydrophobic core** with multiple alkyl substituents \u2192 significant lipophilicity.\n- **H-bonding features:**  \n  - **1 HBD**: the exocyclic **amide NH** (`...CC(=O)NH...`).  \n  - Multiple **carbonyl HB acceptors** (several C=O groups).\n- **Other notable groups:**  \n  - **Trifluoromethyl**-like center (actually a quaternary carbon bearing **CF3**) increases lipophilicity and metabolic stability.  \n  - No obvious **tertiary amine** (classic CYP2D6 inhibition alert).\n- **Size:** Likely **MW ~400\u2013500 Da** (fits the \u201ctypical\u201d range for inhibitors, but size alone isn\u2019t decisive).",
